</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Ulcerative colitis</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><table class="infobox" style="width:22em">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color: lightgrey">Ulcerative colitis</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:UC_granularity.png" class="image"><img alt="UC granularity.png" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/UC_granularity.png/230px-UC_granularity.png" width="230" height="199" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/UC_granularity.png/345px-UC_granularity.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/UC_granularity.png/460px-UC_granularity.png 2x" data-file-width="544" data-file-height="471" /></a>
<div><a href="/wiki/Colonoscopy" title="Colonoscopy">Endoscopic</a> image of a bowel section known as the <a href="/wiki/Sigmoid_colon" title="Sigmoid colon">sigmoid colon</a> afflicted with ulcerative colitis. The internal surface of the colon is blotchy and broken in places.</div>
